# Commit Convention

## Format
<type>(<scope>): <subject>

<body>

## Types
- feat: New feature
- fix: Bug fix
- refactor: Code refactor
- docs: Documentation
- test: Tests
- chore: Build, deps, config

## Scopes (Workspaces)
- agents: Agents workspace
- backend: Backend workspace
- frontend: Frontend workspace

## Example
feat(agents): add memory vector store integration

Integrated OpenAI embeddings with the memory module.
Updated vector_store.py with new indexing logic.

Closes #123

## Branches

### Workspace Branches (Independent)
- workspace/agents: Agents development
- workspace/backend: Backend development
- workspace/frontend: Frontend development

### Shared Branches (Interlinked)
- shared/database: Database schema & migrations (syncs → agents, backend)
- shared/api-calls: API contracts & endpoints (syncs → all workspaces)

### Integration
- main: Production (merges all branches)

## Branch Dependency Graph
```
        main
       /  |  \
      /   |   \
   agents backend frontend
      \   |   /
       shared/
      /    \
  database  api-calls
```

## Workflow

### Workspace Feature
1. git checkout workspace/agents
2. git checkout -b feature/my-feature
3. git commit -m "feat(agents): add new memory function"
4. git push origin feature/my-feature
5. git checkout workspace/agents && git merge feature/my-feature

### Shared Changes (Database/API)
1. git checkout shared/database
2. git checkout -b feature/new-schema
3. git commit -m "feat(database): add users table"
4. git push origin feature/new-schema
5. git checkout shared/database && git merge feature/new-schema
6. Sync to dependent branches:
   git checkout workspace/agents && git merge shared/database
   git checkout workspace/backend && git merge shared/database

### Release to Main
1. git checkout main
2. git merge workspace/agents
3. git merge workspace/backend
4. git merge workspace/frontend
5. git push origin main
